{"paperId": "2e9aad8be8f2bbfe34664a22c2dd1dcdea25279e", "abstract": "Human emotions are expressed through multiple modalities, including verbal and non-verbal information. Moreover, the affective states of human users can be the indicator for the level of engagement and successful interaction, suitable for the robot to use as a rewarding factor to optimize robotic behaviors through interaction. This study demonstrates a multimodal human-robot interaction (HRI) framework with reinforcement learning to enhance the robotic interaction policy and personalize emotional interaction for a human user. The goal is to apply this framework in social scenarios that can let the robots generate a more natural and engaging HRI framework.", "venue": "arXiv.org", "year": 2021, "citationCount": 4, "influentialCitationCount": 0, "openAccessPdf": null, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "A multimodal human-robot interaction (HRI) framework with reinforcement learning is demonstrated to enhance the robotic interaction policy and personalize emotional interaction for a human user."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [-0.0004072314768563956, 0.9094880819320679, -0.3637568950653076, -0.29239875078201294, 0.09038902074098587, 0.3749251961708069, 0.2405862808227539, -0.500545859336853, -0.4542080760002136, 0.476401686668396, 0.45681723952293396, 0.5143688321113586, 0.2519584894180298, 0.17355094850063324, -0.33697912096977234, 0.14579206705093384, -1.2167400121688843, -0.15194803476333618, -0.6649444103240967, -0.8643214106559753, -0.524429976940155, -0.41901662945747375, -1.066872477531433, 0.05796836316585541, 0.07561489939689636, 0.31668704748153687, -0.10260020196437836, 1.0014978647232056, 0.5744574069976807, 0.6952124238014221, 0.5558670163154602, 0.007879168726503849, 0.10150527954101562, 0.04343405365943909, -0.8906058073043823, -0.2749185562133789, -0.2926674783229828, -0.5523139834403992, -0.6083945631980896, 0.5475583672523499, -0.30594107508659363, 0.305730432